news.title: To decongest Bengaluru, government plans AI-driven township in Bidadi
news.para: The Karnataka government has announced plans for Greater Bengaluru Innovation and Tech City (GBIT) in Bidadi, envisioning India's first AI-powered township. This project aims to alleviate pressure on Bengaluru by creating a self-sustaining ecosystem with residential, commercial, and social spaces.

news.title: Noida authority to upload names of property defaulters online
news.para: Noida Authority is set to publish lists of defaulters on its website to enforce transparency and recover long-pending dues from industry, group housing, commercial, and institutional sectors. Recovery proceedings have been initiated against group housing projects with dues exceeding Rs 350 crore.

news.title: Odisha government to hand over work orders for 50,000 homes for poor on Sept 17
news.para: The Odisha government will issue work orders for 50,000 houses under the Antyodaya Gruha Yojana on September 17 to provide permanent housing for economically weaker sections. Launched earlier this year, the scheme complements the PMAY-G, with over 1 lakh beneficiaries already included and further PMAY-G distribution planned for November.

news.title: About 1,014 sq yards plot fetch ₹33.4 crore in Chandigarh
news.para: Chandigarh's real estate market is booming, as evidenced by a recent auction that generated ₹168.85 crore, significantly exceeding the reserve price of ₹75.29 crore. A residential plot in Sector 33 sold for ₹33.4 crore, more than double its reserve price.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto decline in August as recovery stalls
news.para: Greater Toronto Area home sales experienced a slight dip in August, marking the first decline in five months, accompanied by a marginal decrease in prices, according to the Toronto Regional Real Estate Board. Despite lower borrowing costs and selling prices over the past year, affordability remains a challenge for average-income households.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates lenders to meet on Sept 5; challenge process among five bidders likely
news.para: Lenders of the debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) will convene on Friday to discuss the 'challenge process' among five bidders, including Adani Group and Dalmia Bharat, aiming to maximize asset value. This follows a decision to conduct further negotiations with resolution applicants. The minimum bid value is set at Rs 12,000 crore.

news.title: West Bengal cabinet approves policy to convert non-residential plots for real estate, housing purposes
news.para: The West Bengal cabinet has approved a policy allowing conversion of under-utilised non-residential plots for real estate and housing, potentially unlocking land across the state. The decision, applicable to plots under the Urban Development and Municipal Affairs Department, involves a government-determined fee.

news.title: Housing ministry launches unified RERA portal
news.para: The unified RERA portal was launched by the Union Minister of Housing & Urban Affairs, aiming to enhance transparency and facilitate best practice sharing among States/UTs. The council emphasized building a unified nationwide database for real estate projects and urged states to adopt recommendations for stalled projects. They also recommended SoPs to strengthen RERA's functioning and ensure order enforcement.

news.title: After Virar building collapse, civic body to raze 141 unauthorised structures
news.para: Following the tragic collapse of an illegal building in Virar that resulted in 17 fatalities, the Vasai-Virar City Municipal Corporation (VVCMC) has announced plans to demolish 141 unauthorized structures within its jurisdiction. The demolition drive is scheduled to commence on September 8, immediately after the Ganesh festival. VVCMC has mobilized a 50-member demolition squad to carry out the operation.

news.title: Odisha HC rules co-owners can sell undivided shares in property without consent
news.para: Orissa High Court has affirmed that a co-owner can sell their share in a joint property without needing consent from other co-owners. Justice Behera's ruling came after Padmini Barik challenged a sub-registrar's refusal to register her sale deed. The court directed the sub-registrar to accept the deed, reinforcing co-owners' rights under the Transfer of Property Act.

news.title: SC mulls panel to oversee co-developer for Supertech Realtors projects
news.para: The Supreme Court is considering forming a committee to oversee bidding and co-developer selection for Supertech Realtors' stalled Supernova project, aiming to protect homebuyers' interests. The court has paused the process, urging transparency and inviting stakeholder suggestions. This move follows insolvency proceedings against Supertech Realtors, with the court emphasizing the need to resolve issues faced by homebuyers.

news.title: Amazon inks 20-year lease for 5.6 lakh sq ft warehousing space in West Bengal
news.para: Amazon Seller Services has leased over 559,000 sq ft of warehousing space in Hooghly, West Bengal, for 20 years at nearly Rs 430 crore. This deal highlights Amazon's focus on expanding its logistics capacity in key markets due to rising e-commerce demand. The facility will strengthen Amazon's distribution capabilities across eastern India.

news.title: Bain Capital, Colive & Sattva Group launch $100 million co-living platform
news.para: Colive has partnered with Bain Capital and Sattva Group to launch a co-living real estate platform, backed by an initial investment of $100 million. Colive secured $20 million in funding to fuel expansion and market presence. The platform will focus on land acquisition and developing rental housing, with initial projects underway in Pune and Bengaluru.

news.title: Kanodia Cement appoints Anurag Srivastava as CEO
news.para: Kanodia Cement, preparing for its IPO, has appointed Anurag Srivastava as its new CEO, effective August 30. Srivastava brings over 15 years of experience from companies like Wonder Cement, Heidelberg, and Jaypee Cement. He aims to drive innovation and growth for Kanodia Cement as the company seeks to strengthen its position in the industry.

news.title: Land bank, digital planning in Maharashtra’s housing policy to reshape urban future
news.para: Maharashtra govt is launching a new housing policy. It will use a state land bank to increase affordable housing. The policy includes a digital platform for housing information. A district-wise housing demand survey will be conducted by 2026. The policy also focuses on housing for industrial labor and migrant workers.

news.title: Nashik civic body to raise ₹1,000 crore through loans from Asian Development Bank
news.para: Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) plans to borrow ₹1,000 crore from the Asian Development Bank (ADB) for infrastructure projects before the 2026-2028 Simhastha Kumbh Mela. The funds will support sewage and stormwater management, and flood mitigation. NMC has also proposed ₹15,000 crore plan to state government and will raise ₹400 crore through municipal and green bonds.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet gives nod to metro, road projects in Mumbai, Pune, Nagpur
news.para: The Maharashtra cabinet has approved several significant infrastructure projects, including the Wadala-CSMT-Gateway of India metro line in Mumbai and a ring metro in Thane. Additionally, expansions to the Pune and Nagpur Metro systems were sanctioned, along with financial support for suburban rail projects.

news.title: To ease acquisition hurdle, Ghaziabad development body plans to notify township land
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) is set to expedite the Harnandipuram township project by invoking the Land Acquisition Act. Frustrated by slow progress via mutual consent, with only 14 hectares acquired since March, GDA seeks to secure the remaining 470 hectares swiftly.

news.title: ED probe exposes misuse of Dharani for ₹17 crore land fraud
news.para: Enforcement Directorate's investigation uncovers a fraudulent land acquisition scheme in Nagaram village, exploiting the Dharani Portal. A false affidavit claiming sole heirship was accepted without verification, enabling the illegal succession of government land. This manipulation, involving forged documents and bypassed checks, led to the sale of the land for over ₹17.50 crore.
